cyclone.name: HUMBERTO
cyclone.current_location: about 320 mi SE of Freeport, Grand Bahama Island
cyclone.trajectory: Tracking slowly northwest across the central and northwestern Bahamas, then forecast to move along or over the east coast of Florida Saturday before continuing inland across the southeastern United States early next week
cyclone.expected_landfall_location: near the east coast of Florida in the vicinity of Palm Beach County

port.name: Port of Palm Beach District, FL

weather_observation.watch_coast: Jupiter Inlet to the Volusia-Brevard County line, Florida
weather_observation.impacted_coast: East coast of Florida from Jupiter Inlet northward toward Georgia and the Carolinas, and the northwestern Bahamas
weather_observation.wind: Tropical storm–force winds (35–45 mph sustained with higher gusts) are possible beginning early Saturday as the center passes near or over the port.
weather_observation.storm_surge: Significant storm-surge inundation is not anticipated along the Palm Beach County coastline with this system.
weather_observation.rainfall: Periods of heavy rain totaling 2–4 inches could occur Saturday, producing brief localized flooding but totals above 4 inches are unlikely.
weather_observation.other_hazards: Choppy seas and dangerous rip currents are expected ahead of and during the closest approach, impacting vessel movements and berth operations.
